Res(f,g)
f(x)
g(x)
x\mapsto x+\alpha
\overline k,
f(x)=a(x-a_1)\cdots(x-a_m)
g(x)=b(x-x_1)\cdots(x-b_n)
\overline k,
\operatorname{Res}(f,g)=\prod_{i,j}(a_i-b_j).
x'= x+c,
f(x')=a(x'-c-a_1)\cdots(x'-c-a_n)=a(x'-(c+a_1))\cdots(x'-(c+a_n))
g(x')
\operatorname{Res}(f(x'),g(x'))=\prod_{i,j}((c+a_i)-(c+b_j))=\prod_{i,j}(a_i-b_j)
 f(x)=\prod_i(x-\alpha_i) 
F(x)=f(x+\alpha)
G(x)=g(x+\alpha)
F(x)=\prod_i(x-(\alpha_i-\alpha))
\operatorname{Res}(f,g)=\prod_ig(\alpha_i)
\operatorname{Res}(F,G)=\prod_iG(\alpha_i-\alpha)=\prod_ig(\alpha_i)=\operatorname{Res}(f,g)\ .
